SOCKETS
--------
	- A socket is one endpoint of a two way communication link between two programs running on the network. Sockets provide a means of inter-process
	communication (IPC) by establishing named contact points between which the communication take place.
	
	User Space Sockets 
		- stream sockets
		- datagram sockets
	
	Kernel Space Sockets
		- Raw Sockets
		
	
